fter%20sailing%20for%20several%20decades%20or%20experiencing%20a%20catastrophic%20failure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20ships%20can%20still%20be%20valuable%20for%20its%20materials%20or%20be%20retrofitted%20to%20serve%20another%20purpose.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20ships%20are%20outright%20abandoned%20because%20the%20costs%20to%20retrieve%20them%20are%20too%20high.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECruise%20ships%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20are%20expensive%20pieces%20of%20equipment%20to%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthepointsguy.com%2Fguide%2Fcost-to-build-a-cruise-ship%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Points%20Guy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20modern%20cruise%20ships%20can%20cost%20between%20%24500%20million%20to%20%24900%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Royal%20Caribbean's%20Allure%20of%20the%20Seas%2C%20which%20is%20about%201%2C187%20feet%20long%20and%20took%20its%20maiden%20voyage%20in%202010%2C%20cost%20about%20%241.4%20billion%20to%20make%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F1119388%2Franking-expensive-cruise-ships-worldwide-building-cost%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DRoyal%2520Caribbean%2527s%2520Allure%2520of%2520the%2Ccruise%2520ship%2520in%2520the%2520world.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStatista%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20cruise%20ships%20are%20rarely%20outright%20abandoned%20if%20they're%20ever%20decommissioned%20or%20retired%20due%20to%20the%20ship's%20age%20or%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20catastrophic%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOftentimes%2C%20these%20vessels%20are%20taken%20to%20scrapyards%20to%20be%20dismantled%20for%20their%20valuable%20parts%20such%20as%20the%20metal.%20Materials%20from%20a%20single%20ship%20can%20bring%20in%20around%20%244%20million%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%2