in%20the%20US%20Army's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farmypubs.army.mil%2Fepubs%2FDR_pubs%2FDR_a%2FARN30105-AR_360-1-000-WEB-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERegulation%20360-1%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20Public%20Affairs%20Program%2C%26quot%3B%20lies%20a%20small%20note%20that%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BArmy%20aviation%20assets%20are%20not%20to%20be%20used%20to%20transport%20persons%20consumed%20as%20Santa%20Claus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20policy%20also%20notes%20that%20transporting%20people%20in%20costumes%20like%20the%20Easter%20Bunny%20or%20a%20witch%20%E2%80%94%20or%20%26quot%3Bany%20other%20holiday-related%20costume%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20is%20also%20against%20the%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20falls%20under%20a%20section%20that%20addresses%20the%20use%20of%20army%20aircraft%20for%20%26quot%3Bnon%20media%20public%20affairs%20travel%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20military%20blog%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaskandpurpose.com%2Fculture%2Fsanta-banned-army-aircraft%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETask%20%26amp%3B%20Purpose%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20reported.%20The%20policy%20notes%20that%20any%20such%20trip%20must%20be%20approved%20by%20the%20Army%20and%20that%20travelers%20must%20wear%20%26quot%3Bproper%20organizational%20uniforms%2C%20if%20applicable%2C%20and%20must%20present%20proper%20identification.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArmy%20officials%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20Santa%20has%20been%20on%20the%20service's%20%26quot%3BNo-Fly%20List%26quot%3B%20for%20nearly%20a%20quarter%20century.%20They%20said%20the%20regulation's%20%26quot%3Boriginal%20intent%20is%20lost%20to%20the%20ghosts%20of%20Christmas%20Past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20research%2C%20some%20have%20suggested%20that%20the%20regulation%20was%20put%20in%20place%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20propriety%20or%20possibly%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryce%20Dubee%2C%20an%20Army%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20over%20the%20years%20on%20special%20occasions%2C%20hardworking%20Army%20elves%20have%20been%20granted%20exceptions%20to%20the%20policy%20to%20allow%20Kris%20Kringle%20to%20join%20them%20in%20support%20of%20holiday%20missions%2C%20such%20as%20Operation%20Toy%20Drop%20and%20Operation%20Santa%20Claus.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperation%20Toy%20Drop%20is%20an%20annual%20event%20during%20which%20soldiers%20parachute%20to%20the%20ground%20for%20a%20crowd%20of%20spectators.%20Toy%20donations%20are%20also%20collected%2C%20which%20the%20Army%20distributes%20to%20local%20partners%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.armytimes.com%2Fnews%2Fyour-army%2F2018%2F11%2F28%2Fcome-on-down-to-fort-bragg-this-week-for-operation-toy-drop%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArmy%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20event%20is%20an%20exercise%20to%20train%20allied%20jumpmasters%20to%20work%20with%20US%20active%20duty%20and%20Air%20Force%20Reserve%20Command%20paratroopers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jbcharleston.jb.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F234958%2Foperation-toy-drop-combines-forces-training-cheer%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOperation%2520Toy%2520Drop%2520is%2520an%2CMartinez)%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emilitary%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FFeature-Stories%2FStory%2FArticle%2F3227601%2Foperation-santa-claus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOperation%20Santa%20Claus%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20yearly%20community%20relations%20program%20sponsored%20by%20the%20Alaska%20National%20Guard%20that%20provides%20gifts%20to%20children%20in%20remote%20communities%20across%20the%20state.%20In%20partnership%20with%20the%20Salvation%20Army%2C%20the%20program%20delivered%201%2C780%20pounds%20of%20gifts%2C%20backpacks%2C%20hygiene%20supplies%2C%20and%20books%20to%20325%20children%20in%20Scammon%20Bay%2C%20Alaska%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20artic