g%3E%3A%20A%20nasty%20government%2C%20and%20maybe%20the%20word%20nasty%20is%20a%20bit%20editorializing%2C%20but%20a%20determined%20government%20can%20say%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20state%3B%20we%E2%80%99re%20determined%20to%20teach%20the%20government%20in%20Bengal%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20Kerala%20a%20lesson.%20We%20will%20declare%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20We%20will%20then%20use%20the%20power%20of%20parliament%2C%20which%20has%20assumed%20the%20power%20of%20the%20assembly%2C%20to%20divide%20the%20state%20into%20two%20and%20reduce%20both%20hubs%20to%20Union%20territory%20status.%20And%20there%E2%80%99s%20nothing%20anyone%20can%20do%20because%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20set%20a%20precedent%2C%20yeah%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Mr.%20Alok%20Kumar%20Prasanna%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFederalism%20has%20been%20effectively%20threatened%20by%20what%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20decided%20in%20this%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20yeah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20You%20agree%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20yeah%2C%20except%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20have%20to%20decide%20it.%20I%20mean%20if%20they%20keep%20shirking%20the%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20They%20shook%20it%20once%3B%20they%20could%20shirk%20it%20again%20and%20again%20and%20again.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20correct.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20keep%20saying%20that%20they%20should%20have%20decided%20this.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20And%20presumably%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20decide%20it%2C%20they%20now%20need%20a%20seven-judge%20bench%20to%20decide%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Not%20necessary%20because%20they%E2%80%99ve%20said%20that%20it%20can%20be%20decided%20in%20an%20appropriate%20case.%20So%20five%20judges%20can%20say%2C%20well%2C%20this%20is%20an%20appropriate%20case%20so%20we%20are%20deciding%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Except%20they%20have%20to%20first%20agree%20that%20the%20case%20is%20appropriate.%20I%20mean%20the%20most%20appropriate%20case%20is%20the%20one%20they%20consider%20not%20to%20be%20appropriate%3B%20who%20knows%20what%20they%20consider%20to%20be%20appropriate.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yes%2C%20absolutely%2C%20yeah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EKT%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EHindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20makes%20a%20further%20point%2C%20and%20I%20want%20to%20raise%20that%20with%20you.%20They%20made%20it%20in%20the%20leader%20that%20they%20wrote%20on%20the%2012th.%20They%20say%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20suggests%20the%20unconsciously%20questionable%20conclusion%20that%20Parliament%20while%20a%20state%20is%20under%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20can%20do%20any%20act%20legislative%20or%20otherwise%20even%20with%20irreversible%20consequences%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20state%20legislature.%E2%80%9D%20And%20then%20the%20leader%20continues%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20may%20have%20grave%20implications%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20states%3B%20it%20undermines%20federalism%20and%20Democratic%20processes%20to%20a%20frightening%20degree.%E2%80%9D%20As%20I%20read%20that%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20me%20that%20they%E2%80%99ve%20effectively%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20effectively%20opened%20a%20Pandora%E2%80%99s%20box%20of%20problems.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EML%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Yeah%2C%20if%20you%20think%20about%20it%2C%20what%20are%20the%20kinds%20of%20irreversib